? 'The same principle holds true for the water reservoir and pump analogy: without
  a return pipe back to the pond, stored energy in the reservoir cannot be released
  in the form of water flow.  Once the reservoir is completely filled up, no flow
  can occur, no matter how much pressure the pump may generate.  There needs to be
