  \ change the number of protons in an atom's nucleus, and you change the type of\
  \ atom that it is.  In fact, if you could remove three protons from the nucleus\
  \ of an atom of lead, you will have achieved the old alchemists' dream of producing\
  \ an atom of gold!  The tight binding of protons in the nucleus is responsible for\
